content: Rachel Costello is an Irish camogie player who made her senior debut for Dublin in 2009. She represented Dublin at Senior, Junior and Minor levels in 2009. With the Naomh Fionnbarra GAA club in Cabra, she won an Intermediate championship title. Her father Anthony played senior hurling for Dublin and in 2009 scored the winning goal for Naomh Fionnbarra in the Dublin Intermediate championship final when coming on as a substitute.
